name: TM-Items_v11
body: Update with a bunch of dings and a small restructuring to wtmt folders as there are now too many of them to fit on one page. Also too many for one file on github, so you'll have to download the wtmt items and the rest of the items separately.

name: TM-Items_v10
body: WTMT is now a separate download from the rest of the items. If you have an old version of the set and dont want to redownload wtmt, delete all your item folders except A-Ext and A-bExt (& user items here of course), and then only download and unzip the 622mb file from this release.

name: TM_Items_Sorted_v7.0
body:
This update adds the good sets that have come out since the last update, but most importantly the way too many transitions update. This added a lot more road and platform variations, and the road and platform folders were restructured accordingly. I also made my own version of the ground stickers for poles that have better placement settings.

This set may have more objects than the last one, if your game does not load it is because you have reached the 32k limit on objects. This number counts club items, macroblocks, vanilla blocks/items, all custom items/blocks, and possibly other things I am forgetting. Nadeo has reduced the amount of items we have available to use again because they added the console macroblocks and some other things, and nadeo now takes up about ~10k of the limit. This item set contains ~17,000 items. If your game does not start, try removing your club items and existing items and macroblocks, or remove a folder you do not need, such as the inversions folder if you do not build stuff with them.

name: TM_Items_Sorted_V5.0
body: Finally another full release that should be entirely working. Some structural changes come with this if you haven't been keeping up with the beta releases, this is mostly due to the new juice sets. That said it's in a state now where I won't be making any more drastic changes for the foreseeable future, at least until rxelux's wonder plugin is released.
